stimulusHtml: Which of the following best describes the behavior of the method?

features.html:
Consider the following method. 

 

public static boolean mystery(ArrayList<Integer> numbers)
{
   int prev = Integer.MAX_VALUE;
   for (int num : numbers)
   {
      if (num > prev)
      {
         return false;
      }
      prev = num;
   }
   return true;
}

choicesHtml: It returns  false  if  numbers  is sorted from least to greatest and returns  true  otherwise.
It returns  false  if  numbers  is sorted from greatest to least and returns  true  otherwise.
It returns  true  if  numbers  is sorted from least to greatest and returns  false  otherwise.
It returns  true  if  numbers  is sorted from greatest to least and returns  false  otherwise.
